    <summary>Explorer thumbnails for 313 file types Windows can't read, plus a right-click image toolkit.</summary>
    <description>
**SageThumbs 2K** is a modern, crash-isolated Windows 11 shell extension (written in Rust) that rebuilds the classic SageThumbs. It gives File Explorer thumbnails for **313 file types** Windows can't preview on its own — camera RAW, HEIC/AVIF, Photoshop, DjVu, ebooks &amp; comics, video frames, 3D-print files, and a long tail of obscure formats — plus a right-click image toolkit (convert, resize, rotate, OCR, color picker, metadata strip, combine-to-PDF/CBZ) and a console/AI CLI.

* 100% clean-room Rust — no spyware, no personal data (just an anonymous install count).
* Crash-isolated: runs in Explorer's sandboxed thumbnail host so a bad file can't take down your shell.
* Free for personal use (PolyForm Noncommercial 1.0.0); commercial use needs a separate license.

> Note: the installer is not code-signed, so Windows SmartScreen may show a one-time "unknown publisher" prompt during install (click *More info → Run anyway*).
    </description>
    <releaseNotes>https://github.com/LunarWerxs/SageThumbs-2k/blob/main/docs/CHANGELOG.md</releaseNotes>
